Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
find_global(25.10)                                          find_global(25.10)

Name
       find_global - Returns all the public variables

Syntax
        find_global

       [-help]

       [<pattern> | -non_default ]

       [[-tcl  ]  |  [[-name  ]  [-value  ]  [-type  ]  [-default  ]  [-info ]
       [-range_or_enum ] [-transient ]]]

       Returns all the public variables. If  you  want  to  retrieve  specific
       global variables, you can use patterns with this command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each find_global parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man find_global.

       <pattern>
              Specifies  a  string with wildcards that can be used to retrieve
              specific global variables.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -default
              Displays the default value of variables. If a pattern is  speci-
              fied, displays default value of all variables matching the spec-
              ified pattern.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -info  Displays  the  description  of variables. If a pattern is speci-
              fied, displays description of all variables matching the  speci-
              fied pattern.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -name  Displays the name of all or specified global variables.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -non_default
              Displays the list of variables whose values are not default.

              Note:  If  neither  pattern,  nor -non_default is specified, the
              tool displays all variables.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -range_or_enum
              Displays the range or legal enum value list, if they exist,  for
              all or specified global variables.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -tcl   Returns  a  tcl list that has every field value of the specified
              variables. If a pattern is not specified, displays this informa-
              tion for all global variables.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -transient
              Displays whether the specified variable is transient. If a  pat-
              tern  is not specified, displays this information for all global
              variables.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -type  Displays the type (Boolean, Integer, String,  Enum)  of  all  or
              specified variables.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -value Displays the current value of all or specified variables.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command returns all public variables and private
                variables with a non-default value:

                find_global

              * The following command returns all public global variables (and
                private  variables  with  a  non-default value) beginning with
                dbg.

                find_global dbg*

                Output:

                dbgAllowInferredTriStateArcs 1 # (Integer, default=1,  persis-
                tent)

                 #  Controls whether arcs from a tristate enable to a inferred
                as tristate

                 # enable and disable arcs if they are not  explicitly  speci-
                fied by the Liberty

                 # timing_type attribute. This functionality is mainly to sup-
                port older

                 # modeling styles in legacy libraries.

                dbgConvertSetupHoldOnAsyncToRecRem  1  #  (Integer, default=1,
                persistent)

                 # Controls whether single-edged  setup  and  hold  checks  on
                asynchronous pins

                 # in the Liberty library are inferred as recovery and removal
                checks. This

                 #  is  mainly  to support older modeling styles in legacy li-
                braries.

                dbgPicoSecPerDBU 0.1 # (Double, default=0.1, persistent)

                 # Controls how timing library numbers are  internally  scaled
                to database

                 #  units.  The  default is 1/10 pS per DBU. To represent very
                large delay

                 # numbers accurately this value can be increased  as  needed.
                This variable

                 # should be set before timing libraries are read.

                dbgUseDuplicateTimeArc 1 # (Integer, default=1, persistent)

                 # This variable controls whether or not redundant timing arcs
                (no retain

                 #  or  conditional  variance) are supported. This variable is
                obsolete and

                 # will be removed from future releases of the software.

              * The following command returns information on a specific  vari-
                able, lefDefOutVersion.

                find_global lefDefOutVersion

                The output is as follows:

                lefDefOutVersion "" # (String, default="", persistent)

                 #  Specify  LEF/DEF output version. Possible string value are
                5.3, 5.4, 5.5,

                 # 5.6, 5.7 and 5.8.

              * The following command returns names  and  default  information
                for all global variables starting with the pattern def.

                find_global def* -name -default

                The output is as follows:

